article.description: S. Carolina St. 81, Coastal Carolina 80, OT
article.headline: S. Carolina St. 81, Coastal Carolina 80, OT
article.linkText: S. Carolina St. 81, Coastal Carolina 80, OT
article.story: ORANGEBURG, S.C. (AP) -- Derrick Davis scored six of his 13 points in overtime to help South Carolina State beat Coastal Carolina 81-80 on Wednesday night. The largest lead for either team in the game came at 9:03, when a 3-pointer by Coastal Carolina's Jack Leasure put the Chanticleers (3-4) seven points ahead, 16-23. But the Bulldogs (2-6) led 37-36 at the half. In the second half, the Bulldogs led by as many as seven points with 7:13 left in the half. But a 3-pointer by Chanticleer Joshua Mack tied the game with 0:43 left in the game. Travis Jones led the Bulldogs with 22 points, followed by Jason Flagler with 16 points and a team-high seven rebounds in the game. Brian Mason joined Davis with points. Moses Sonko led the Chanticleers' scoring with 22 points and four rebounds, while Mack scored a career-high 19 points -- 12 in the second half and seven in overtime. Jack Leasure added 19 points, including five 3-pointers, and tied for a game-high eight rebounds. The Chanticleers were 31-of-60 (51.7 percent) from the field, while the Bulldogs were 27-of-57 (47.4 percent) from the floor.
